<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="11" pageNumber="590" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[685,1173,194,1729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,820,1655,1676]" pageId="11" pageNumber="590">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[835,1068,1655,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[835,1068,1655,1676]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="590">Hoplopyga albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from nearly all other 
<taxonomicName authority="species" authorityName="SPECIES" box="[986,1171,1682,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[986,1093,1682,1703]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="590">Hoplopyga</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having a protibia with two teeth near the apex
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[173,660,194,932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">
(
<figureCitation box="[180,272,194,216]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[197,237,1581,1600]" captionTargetBox="[175,1191,194,1560]" captionTargetId="figure-1@10.[172,1194,191,1564]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 7–12. Hoplopyga albiventris. 7–8) Habitus; 9) Mesometasternal process, ventral view; 10–11) Parameres; 12) Distribution." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6553847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6553847/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
). It shares this trait with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="2008" box="[518,615,194,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gosseti">
<emphasis box="[518,615,194,215]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. gosseti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these two species can be separated by the shape of the pronotum. The lateral margins of the pronotum are obtusely angulate and appear rounded in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[173,304,301,322]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[173,304,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="2008" box="[402,498,301,322]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gosseti">
<emphasis box="[402,498,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. gosseti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterolateral margins of the pronotum subparallel. In addition, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[268,404,354,375]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[268,404,354,375]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two yellow spots on the ventral face of the mesometasternal process that are absent in 
<emphasis box="[353,459,407,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="2008" box="[353,456,407,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gosseti">H. gosseti</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the sternites of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[173,300,433,454]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[173,300,433,454]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mostly cream-colored or brownish yellow, while the sternites of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="2008" box="[456,551,460,481]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gosseti">
<emphasis box="[456,551,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. gosseti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are largely reddish brown and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="591" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[173,660,194,932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,346,513,534]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Nomenclature.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Antoine" box="[360,516,513,534]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" pagination="241 - 256" refId="ref35987" refString="Antoine, P. 2008. Contribution a la connaissance du genre Hoplopyga J. Thomson (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae). Coleopteres 14: 241 - 256." type="journal article" year="2008">Antoine (2008)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gory and Percheron" authorityYear="1833" box="[173,308,540,561]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Gymnetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscorubra">
<emphasis box="[173,308,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">G. fuscorubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[368,501,540,561]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[368,501,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we concur with this synonymy; putative 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gory and Percheron" authorityYear="1833" box="[460,595,566,587]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Gymnetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscorubra">
<emphasis box="[460,595,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">G. fuscorubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens are simply a reddish form of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[517,649,593,614]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[517,649,593,614]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[173,660,194,932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,365,619,640]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Natural History.</emphasis>
Specimens have been caught at elevations ranging from sea level to 
<quantity box="[526,602,646,667]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" unit="m" value="1300.0">1,300 m</quantity>
(label data). 
<bibRefCitation author="Luederwaldt" box="[232,416,672,693]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" pagination="405 - 413" refId="ref36932" refString="Luederwaldt, G. 1911. Quatro lamellicorneos termitophilos. Revista do Museu Paulista 8: 405 - 413." type="journal article" year="1911">Luederwaldt (1911)</bibRefCitation>
discovered 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[531,659,672,693]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[531,659,672,693]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae in the mounds of 
<taxonomicName box="[443,659,699,720]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Cornitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[443,573,699,720]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Cornitermes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(Isoptera) feeding on the walls of the nest. Adults were observed feeding on the sap of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spreng" authorityName="Spreng" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Baccharis rufescens</emphasis>
Spreng
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[402,575,778,800]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[402,493,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Vernonia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
flowers (both 
<taxonomicName box="[226,327,805,826]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Luederwaldt" box="[344,513,805,826]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" pagination="405 - 413" refId="ref36932" refString="Luederwaldt, G. 1911. Quatro lamellicorneos termitophilos. Revista do Museu Paulista 8: 405 - 413." type="journal article" year="1911">Luederwaldt 1911</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di Iorio" box="[522,650,805,826]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" pagination="281 - 318" refId="ref36308" refString="Di Iorio, O. 2014. A review of the natural history of adult Cetoniinae (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) from Argentina and adjacent countries. Zootaxa 3790: 281 - 318." type="journal article" year="2014">Di Iorio 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Puker" box="[173,363,832,853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" refId="ref37493" refString="Puker, A., H. L. Ad ' vincula, V. Korasaki, F. N. F. Ferreira, and J. Orozco. 2014. Biodiversity of Cetoniinae beetles (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae) in introduced and native habitats in the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Entomological Science. doi: 10.1111 / ens. 12069." type="book" year="2014">
Puker 
<emphasis box="[237,290,832,853]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
compared species abundance in different habitats in 
<collectingCountry box="[423,484,858,879]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and only found 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory and Percheron" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[173,310,885,906]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis box="[173,310,885,906]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">H. albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pastureland where 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Cornitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="12" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[538,659,885,906]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="591">Cornitermes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
termite mounds were common.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
